[{"html":"<blockquote>\n<p>All documentations are under active work and subject to change soon!</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span id=\"Application_Integration\" class=\"offset-anchor\" ></span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"integrate#Application_Integration\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"> <i class=\"las la-link\"></i> </a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tApplication Integration\n\t\t\t\t\t</h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span id=\"Service_Integration\" class=\"offset-anchor\" ></span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"integrate#Service_Integration\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"> <i class=\"las la-link\"></i> </a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tService Integration\n\t\t\t\t\t</h3>","metadata":{"title":"Overview","description":"..."},"subsections":[{"slug":"Application_Integration","title":"Application Integration","level":3},{"slug":"Service_Integration","title":"Service Integration","level":3}],"slug":"Overview","file":"00-overview.en.md"},{"html":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span id=\"Client_Types_Profiles\" class=\"offset-anchor\" ></span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"integrate#Client_Types_Profiles\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"> <i class=\"las la-link\"></i> </a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tClient Types / Profiles\n\t\t\t\t\t</h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span id=\"Single_Page_Application\" class=\"offset-anchor\" ></span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"integrate#Single_Page_Application\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"> <i class=\"las la-link\"></i> </a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tSingle Page Application\n\t\t\t\t\t</h4><p>If your <a href=\"administrate#Clients\">client</a> is a single page application (SPA) we recommend that you use <a href=\"documentation#Authorization_Code\">Authorization Code</a> with <a href=\"documentation#Proof_Key_for_Code_Exchange\">Proof Key for Code Exchange</a>.</p>\n<p>This flow has great support with most modern languages and frameworks.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In the OIDC and OAuth world this <strong>client profile</strong> is called &quot;user-agent-based application&quot;</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span id=\"Server_Side_Application\" class=\"offset-anchor\" ></span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"integrate#Server_Side_Application\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"> <i class=\"las la-link\"></i> </a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tServer Side Application\n\t\t\t\t\t</h4><p>In the OIDC and OAuth world this client profile is called &quot;web application&quot;</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span id=\"Mobile_App_Native_App\" class=\"offset-anchor\" ></span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"integrate#Mobile_App_Native_App\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"> <i class=\"las la-link\"></i> </a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tMobile App / Native App\n\t\t\t\t\t</h4><p>In the OIDC and OAuth world this client profile is called &quot;native application&quot;</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span id=\"How_to_consume_authorizations_in_your_application_or_service\" class=\"offset-anchor\" ></span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"integrate#How_to_consume_authorizations_in_your_application_or_service\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\"> <i class=\"las la-link\"></i> </a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tHow to consume authorizations in your application or service\n\t\t\t\t\t</h3><p>With ZITADEL you can manage the <a href=\"administrate#Roles\">roles</a> a <a href=\"administrate#Projects\">project</a> supplies to your users in the form of authorizations.\nOn the <a href=\"administrate#Projects\">project</a> it can be configured how <strong>project roles</strong> are supplied to the <a href=\"administrate#Clients\">clients</a>.\nBy default ZITADEL asserts the claim <strong>projectrole</strong> to the <a href=\"documentation#userinfo_endpoint\">userinfo_endpoint</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Assert the claim <strong>projectrole</strong> to <strong>access_token</strong></li>\n<li>Assert the claim <strong>projectrole</strong> to <strong>id_token</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=''><pre class='language-undefined'><code>{\n\t<span class=\"hljs-attr\">&quot;projectroles&quot;</span>: [{\n\t\t<span class=\"hljs-attr\">&quot;user&quot;</span>: [<span class=\"hljs-string\">&quot;orgid1&quot;</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\">&quot;orgid1&quot;</span>]\n\t}]\n}</code></pre></div><p>For more details about how <strong>ZITADEL</strong> treats <a href=\"documentation#Scopes\">scopes</a> and <a href=\"documentation#Claims\">claims</a> see the <a href=\"documentation\">documentations</a>.</p>\n","metadata":{"title":"OpenID Connect & OAuth","description":"..."},"subsections":[{"slug":"Client_Types_Profiles","title":"Client Types / Profiles","level":3},{"slug":"Single_Page_Application","title":"Single Page Application","level":4},{"slug":"Server_Side_Application","title":"Server Side Application","level":4},{"slug":"Mobile_App_Native_App","title":"Mobile App / Native App","level":4},{"slug":"How_to_consume_authorizations_in_your_application_or_service","title":"How to consume authorizations in your application or service","level":3}],"slug":"OpenID_Connect_and_OAuth","file":"01-openidoauth.en.md"}]